{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}

{% block content %}
  {% with summary = {"title": "Cycle time", "headline": cycle_time.headline} %}
    {% include "_partials/metric_summary.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  {% with mode = 'detail', data = cycle_time %}
    {% include "_partials/cycle_time_tile.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  {% with data = work_items %}
    {% include "_partials/work_items_table.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  <section class="detail-extras">
    <h2>How to read this</h2>
    <p>
      Each point is one completed work item plotted at its
      <em>completion date (UTC)</em> against its <em>cycle time</em>
      (days from open to merge). The reference lines are the
      empirical percentiles of cycle time across all completed
      items in this window: P50 (median), P85 (Vacanti's external
      commitment threshold), and P95 (high-stakes commitment).
    </p>

    <h2>Caveats</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Percentiles are empirical — read from the items completed
        in this window, not Monte Carlo simulated.</li>
      <li>Outliers shift P85 / P95 up. A single stuck-then-finished
        item can swing the deep-tail percentiles.</li>
      <li>Intra-day x-position is random (jitter within the day
        column); the date in the tooltip is the truth.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Cycle time = <code>completed_at − created_at</code> in days.
      Per-item details and the canonical definitions live in
      <a href="https://github.com/dvhthomas/flowmetrics/blob/main/docs/METRICS.md">METRICS.md</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Actions</h2>
    <p><em>Reserved for future "now what?" suggestions — filter presets,
       experiment ideas, drill-into-outliers. Empty in v1.</em></p>
  </section>

  <a class="back-link" href="{{ ("/workflows/" ~ contract.name ~ "/") | keep_filters }}">← Back to dashboard</a>
{% endblock %}
